Takeaways:
  * No 'messages' exist at the model layer — only this token stream.
  * Role headers (`<|im_start|>user`) ARE tokens; the model learned
    that pattern during training, that's how it knows whose turn it is.
  * Tool schemas live INSIDE the prompt as text; the model generates
    a tool call by emitting tokens that match a learned tool-call format,
    which the SDK then parses into structured `tool_calls`.

